    {
        "content": "<p>if you have <code>↑⟨h, ⋯⟩</code> in your goal then they cancel out and it's just equal to <code>h</code></p>",
        "id": 570666545,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1769637014
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but you can't just get rid of the brackets directly</p>",
        "id": 570666591,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1769637031
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I see, so coercing the element into belonging to the superset?</p>",
        "id": 570666725,
        "sender_full_name": "Tarun Nair",
        "timestamp": 1769637096
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>you can start by introducing <code>↑</code>s into your goal (in this case it's <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Subtype.val#doc\">docs#Subtype.val</a>) using <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Subtype.ext#doc\">docs#Subtype.ext</a> or with the <code>ext</code> tactic</p>",
        "id": 570666736,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
